      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOMAX KEEPING (2) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 3 lengths at this track in a handy 18.10. Fair draw can see a good run and has the ability and in winning form. Has a strong record out of this box with three wins and a minor placing from four starts. Hard to fault his form and he makes plenty of appeal. BUGATTI RICO (1) is progressing well and looks close to another win after hitting the frame from Box 7 last run (18.52) at this track. Has a strong record out of this box with five wins and two minor placings from 12 starts. Expecting another good run. CREEPING TIGER (6) goes very well at the distance with three wins and a placing from five starts. Recorded a 6 length win (18.11) in a Grade 5 last time at this track. With even luck and a clean start should be around the money. RED ROCK ALONG (3) comes off a (18.52) win last time, scoring by a nose in a Grade 5 over 320m at this track. Yet to taste defeat in two runs from this draw.",
